<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.198430>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Dorsal and lateral habitus of Oocyclus species found in the Venezuelan Andes region. A) O. meridensis sp. n.; B) O. trujillo sp. n.; C) O. andinus sp. n.; D) O. pico sp. n. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/198430/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.198433>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Aedeagi of Oocyclus species. A) O. petra sp. n., B) O. galbus sp. n.; C) O. pico sp. n. D) O. bolivari sp. n. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/198433/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.198434>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Distribution of Oocyclus species in Venezuela." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/198434/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.198435>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Habitat of Oocyclus species. A) Aragua State, collecting event AS- 06 - 023; type locality for O. pico and O. pittieri, locality for O. sapphirus. B) Zulia State, near Toromo, collecting event AS- 07 - 022, type locality for O. galbus and locality for O. substillus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/198435/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

